    Property Classes

    Usage:
    - Use these classes to apply flexbox properties to elements based on browser width
    - Add propertyName={["xs" || "sm" || "md" || "lg"]} to your Flexbox container or column
    - The size(s) will determine where the property is applied to the element
    - For example: <Flexbox md={4} showAt={["md", "lg"]}> means the element will be 4 columns wide and only visible at the md and lg sizes
    - Conversely: <Flexbox xs={12} showAt={["xs", "sm"]}> means the element will be 12 columns wide and only be visible at the xs and sm sizes

    Sizes to approximate browser width
    - xs: ~767px or less
    - sm: ~768px - 991px
    - md: ~992px - 1199px
    - lg: ~1200px or more

    Note:
    - The double declaration of text-align in the start/end classes is to support older IE and Edge browsers that don't support Flexbox start and end features

/* New badge marker - based on .cal-item-tag for Calendar */

.badge-new-marker {
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    padding: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #daf200;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: #0a1f2e;
}

/* Repeatable count indicator */

.badge-repeatable {
    font-size: 12px;
    position: absolute;
    color: #888;
}

.badge-repeatable:before {
    content: '\00d7';
}

.badge-repeatable, a:hover .badge-repeatable {
    color: #888;
}

/* Badge thumbnail */

.badge-thumbnail {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
    text-align: center;
}

.badge-thumbnail:hover {
    text-decoration: none;
}

.badge-thumbnail .badge-new-marker {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
}

.badge-thumbnail .badge-img {
    width: 80px;
    height: 93px;
}

.badge-thumbnail .badge-name {
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.2em;
    margin-top: 7px;
}

.badge-thumbnail .badge-repeatable {
    top: 74px;
    left: 86px;
}

/* Available badge effect */

.badge-available .badge-img {
    opacity: 0.5;
    -webkit-filter: grayscale(100%);
    /* Safari 6.0 - 9.0 */
    filter: grayscale(100%);
}

/* Badge Lists */

.badge-summary .badge-name {
    font-weight: 600;
}

.badge-summary .badge-points:after {
    content: '  ';
}

/* Avatar badge level indicators */

.avatar.avatar-medium + .badge-level.level-sm {
    position: absolute;
    margin-top: -16px;
    margin-left: 64px;
}

/* Badge detail modals */

.badge-detail, .related-badges-list, .connections-with-badge {
    max-width: 470px;
    margin-right: auto;
    margin-left: auto;
}

.badge-detail {
    text-align: center;
}

.badge-detail a {
    cursor: pointer;
    color: #1265c2;
}

.badge-detail .badge-img {
    width: 300px;
    margin-bottom: 11px;
}

.badge-detail .badge-progress {
    font-size: 12px;
    margin: 0 auto;
}

.badge-detail .badge-progress .progress-bar {
    display: block;
    width: 100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
}

.badge-detail .badge-progress-label {
    line-height: 1.2em;
    margin-top: 5px;
}

.badge-detail .badge-summary {
    margin-top: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
}

.badge-detail .badge-name {
    font-weight: 600;
}

.badge-detail .badge-earned-msg {
    margin-bottom: 22px;
}

.badge-detail .badge-earned-msg-list {
    margin: 11px auto 0;
}

.badge-detail .badge-earned-msg-list li:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
}

.badge-detail .badge-earned-msg-list li {
    float: left;

    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
}

.badge-detail .badge-earned-msg-list li div {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    padding: 8px;
}

.badge-detail .badge-earned-msg-list li .badge-date {

    text-align: left;
}

.badge-detail .badge-earned-msg-list li .badge-event {
    float: right;
    width: 60%;

}

/*  ======================
        Badge Level Indicator - based on http://csshexagon.com
        ======================  */

.badge-level {
    position: relative;
    display: block;
    text-align: left;
}

.badge-level:before, .badge-level:after {
    position: absolute;
    width: 0;
    content: '';
    border-right: solid transparent;
    border-left: solid transparent;
}

.badge-level:before {
    bottom: 100%;
    border-bottom-style: solid;
}

.badge-level:after {
    top: 100%;
    width: 0;
    border-top-style: solid;
}

.badge-level span {
    font-weight: bold;
    position: absolute;
    width: 100%;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
    text-shadow: 0 0 2px #000;
}

/* Badge level sizes */

.badge-level.level-sm {
    width: 16px;
    height: 9.24px;
    margin: 4.62px 0;
}

.badge-level.level-sm:before, .badge-level.level-sm:after {
    border-right-width: 8px;
    border-left-width: 8px;
}

.badge-level.level-sm:before {
    border-bottom-width: 4.62px;
}

.badge-level.level-sm:after {
    border-top-width: 4.62px;
}

.badge-level.level-sm span {
    font-size: 10px;
    line-height: 9.24px;
}

.badge-level.level-md {
    width: 26px;
    height: 15.01px;
    margin: 7.51px 0;
}

.badge-level.level-md:before, .badge-level.level-md:after {
    border-right-width: 13px;
    border-left-width: 13px;
}

.badge-level.level-md:before {
    border-bottom-width: 7.51px;
}

.badge-level.level-md:after {
    border-top-width: 7.51px;
}

.badge-level.level-md span {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 15.01px;
}

.badge-level.level-xl {
    width: 173px;
    height: 99.88px;
    margin: 49.94px 0;
}

.badge-level.level-xl:before, .badge-level.level-xl:after {
    border-right-width: 86.5px;
    border-left-width: 86.5px;
}

.badge-level.level-xl:before {
    border-bottom-width: 49.94px;
}

.badge-level.level-xl:after {

            ======================  */

/* Badge name vertical truncate */

}

.badge-name.line-clamp {
    -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
}

/*  ======================
        Badge shimmer effect - based on http://jsfiddle.net/AntonTrollback/nqQc7
        ======================  */

.badge-earned .badge-thumbnail {
    overflow: hidden;
}

.badge-earned .badge-thumbnail:after {
    position: absolute;
    top: -110%;
    left: -210%;
    width: 200%;
    height: 200%;
    content: '';
    transform: rotate(30deg);
    opacity: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
        to right,
        rgba(255, 255, 255, 0) 0%,
        rgba(255, 255, 255, 0) 77%,
        rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5) 92%,
        rgba(255, 255, 255, 0) 100%
    );
}

/* Match sidebar background color */

.border-wrapper .badge-earned .badge-thumbnail:after {
    background: linear-gradient(
        to right,
        rgba(250, 250, 250, 0) 0%,
        rgba(250, 250, 250, 0) 77%,
        rgba(250, 250, 250, 0.5) 92%,
        rgba(250, 250, 250, 0) 100%
    );
}

/* Hover state - trigger effect */

.badge-earned .badge-thumbnail:hover:after {
    top: -30%;
    left: -30%;
    transition-timing-function: ease;
    transition-duration: 0.7s, 0.7s, 0.15s;
    transition-property: left, top, opacity;
    opacity: 1;
}

/* Active state */

.badge-earned .badge-thumbnail:active:after {
    opacity: 0;
}

/* Z-index stuff so shimmer effect only shows in badge img */

.badge-earned .badge-thumbnail:after {
    z-index: 1;
}

.badge-earned .badge-thumbnail span, .badge-earned .badge-thumbnail div {
    z-index: 2;
}

.badge-earned .badge-thumbnail .badge-name {
    position: relative;
}

.page.activity-detail .weather *, .page.activity-detail .weather.large * {
    -webkit-transition: 150ms cubic-bezier(0.175, 0.885, 0.305, 1.24);
    transition: 150ms cubic-bezier(0.175, 0.885, 0.305, 1.24);

}

    line-height: 21px;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    border: 1px solid #222;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-right: 0;
}

.page.activity-detail .weather .wind:before {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    width: 0;
    height: 15px;
    border-width: 7px 3px;
    border-style: solid;
    border-color: #222 transparent transparent transparent;
    position: absolute;
    top: -4px;
    left: 8px;
}

/*
    .page.activity-detail .wind-n:before {
        nothing needed - north is the default
    }
    */

.page.activity-detail .wind-nne:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(22.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(22.5deg);
    transform: rotate(22.5deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-ne:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(45deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(45deg);
    transform: rotate(45deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-ene:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(77.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(77.5deg);
    transform: rotate(77.5deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-e:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(90deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(90deg);
    transform: rotate(90deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-ese:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(112.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(112.5deg);
    transform: rotate(112.5deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-se:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(135deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(135deg);
    transform: rotate(135deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-sse:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(157.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(157.5deg);
    transform: rotate(157.5deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-s:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(180deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(180deg);
    transform: rotate(180deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-ssw:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(202.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(202.5deg);
    transform: rotate(202.5deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-sw:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(225deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(225deg);
    transform: rotate(225deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-wsw:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(247.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(247.5deg);
    transform: rotate(247.5deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-w:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(270deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(270deg);
    transform: rotate(270deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-wnw:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(292.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(292.5deg);
    transform: rotate(292.5deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-nw:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(315deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(315deg);
    transform: rotate(315deg);
}

.page.activity-detail .wind-nnw:before {
    -webkit-transform: rotate(337.5deg);
    -ms-transform: rotate(337.5deg);
    transform: rotate(337.5deg);
}

class="">Help</h3></div><div tabindex="0" class="Dialog_dialogBody__BSWzp"><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_h3__yDUiE">Self Evaluation</span><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_h5__0oSZK">With the self evaluation tools in Garmin Connect, you can create a better overall record of each activity by rating your perceived effort level and how good you felt while performing it.</span><div class="marBottomSM"></div><div class="Accordion_accordionItemContainer__pAxDg"><button type="button" class="Accordion_summaryContainer__xmGIq " aria-expanded="false"><span><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_selfEvaluationAccordionTitle__kFSSY">How did you feel?</span></span><span class="Accordion_summaryIcon__wboZO false"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="currentColor" data-library="ui-icons" viewBox="0 0 24 24" height="14px" width="14px"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 14.586 4.707 7.293 3.293 8.707 12 17.414l8.707-8.707-1.414-1.414L12 14.586Z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></span></button><div class="Accordion_detailsContainer__mcwXN Accordion_closed__Rf8pq" style="max-height: 0px;"><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_h3__yDUiE">Rating Your Feelings</span><p>We all have good and bad training days, and youre not going to feel your best during every activity. With How Did You Feel?, you can document these feelings for each activity and provide further historic insight to your overall training log.</p><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_h5__0oSZK">Perspective on Performance</span><p>As you look back at your training log, you may wonder why your performance on a particular day was strong, but weak the following day. By documenting how you felt, you can begin to discern patterns to help you train smarter in the future.</p><p>Each activity can be ranked on a five-point scale from "Very Weak" to "Very Strong." On some devices, you may be prompted to rate how you feel when you save your activity. You can also add or change How Did You Feel? later by editing the activity in Garmin Connect.</p></div></div><div class="Accordion_accordionItemContainer__pAxDg"><button type="button" class="Accordion_summaryContainer__xmGIq " aria-expanded="false"><span><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_selfEvaluationAccordionTitle__kFSSY">Perceived Effort</span></span><span class="Accordion_summaryIcon__wboZO false"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="currentColor" data-library="ui-icons" viewBox="0 0 24 24" height="14px" width="14px"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 14.586 4.707 7.293 3.293 8.707 12 17.414l8.707-8.707-1.414-1.414L12 14.586Z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></span></button><div class="Accordion_detailsContainer__mcwXN Accordion_closed__Rf8pq" style="max-height: 0px;"><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_h3__yDUiE">How Hard Did You Work?</span><p>Perceived effort lets you measure on a scale of 1-10 the amount of effort you think you put into a specific activity. The scale ranges from Very Light to Maximum.</p><span class="WorkoutExecutionMetrics_h4__2dkMA">Tracking Effort</span><p>Logging your perceived effort for each run or ride can lend further insight to your training log. It also indicates if the workout had a maintaining or improving effect on your fitness level. Steady workouts at a moderate effort or workouts involving longer intervals (&gt;180 sec) have a positive impact on aerobic metabolism and produce an aerobic Training Effect.</p><p>If you have more than one activity in a day, Garmin Connect will display your highest aerobic Training Effect value in graphs where it appears.</p></div></div><div class="Accordion_accordionItemContainer__pAxDg"><button type="button" class="Accordion_summaryContainer__xmGIq " aria-expanded="false"><span><p>Anaerobic</p></span><span class="Accordion_summaryIcon__wboZO false"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="currentColor" data-library="ui-icons" viewBox="0 0 24 24" height="14px" width="14px"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 14.586 4.707 7.293 3.293 8.707 12 17.414l8.707-8.707-1.414-1.414L12 14.586Z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></span></button><div class="Accordion_detailsContainer__mcwXN Accordion_closed__Rf8pq" style="max-height: 0px;"><h4>High-Intensity Improvements</h4><p>Anaerobic Training Effect uses heart rate and speed (or power) to determine how a workout affects your ability to perform at a very high intensity. Repeated high-intensity intervals of 10 to 120 seconds have an especially beneficial impact on your anaerobic capability and result in an anaerobic Training Effect.</p><p>If you have more than one activity in a day, Garmin Connect will display your highest anaerobic Training Effect value in graphs where it appears.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="Dialog_dialogBackdrop__PnNPL "></div></div></div>
